  <div class="section-num">01</div>
  <div>
    <div class="section-title">What Even IS Recursion? — The Mirror Trick 🪞</div>
    <div class="section-desc">One idea. Two mirrors. Infinite reflections — but we stop before infinity.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="fun-box fun-box-yellow">
  <span class="emoji-big">🪞</span><strong>Stand between two mirrors in a barber shop.</strong><br>
  You see yourself reflected in the mirror, which reflects in the other mirror, which reflects again... forever?<br><br>
  <strong>Recursion is the same idea — but in code.</strong> A function calls ITSELF. But unlike the mirrors, we tell it when to STOP. That stopping point is called the <strong>base case</strong>.
</div>

<div class="diagram-wrap">
  <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.07em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink3);margin-bottom:12px;">THE BIG IDEA — a recursive function has exactly 2 parts</div>
  <svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 680 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
    <defs>
      <marker id="arr" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M2 1L8 5L2 9" fill="none" stroke="context-stroke" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
      </marker>
    </defs>
    <!-- Function box -->
    <rect x="200" y="30" width="280" height="140" rx="12" fill="#E6F1FB" stroke="#85B7EB" stroke-width="2"/>
    <text x="340" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Mono,monospace" font-size="13" fill="#185FA5" font-weight="500">def my_function(n):</text>
    <!-- base case -->
    <rect x="220" y="62" width="240" height="36" rx="6" fill="#EAF3DE" stroke="#97C459" stroke-width="2"/>
    <text x="340" y="77" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Mono,monospace" font-size="11" fill="#3B6D11">if n == 0:  # BASE CASE 🛑</text>
    <text x="340" y="91" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Mono,monospace" font-size="11" fill="#3B6D11">    return 1</text>
    <!-- general case -->
    <rect x="220" y="106" width="240" height="36" rx="6" fill="#FAEEDA" stroke="#EF9F27" stroke-width="2"/>
    <text x="340" y="121" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Mono,monospace" font-size="11" fill="#633806">else:  # GENERAL CASE 🔁</text>
    <text x="340" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Mono,monospace" font-size="11" fill="#633806">    return n * my_function(n-1)</text>
    <!-- Arrow looping back -->
    <path d="M480 123 Q580 123 580 85 Q580 30 480 30" stroke="#633806" fill="none" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6,3" marker-end="url(#arr)"/>
    <text x="590" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#633806">calls itself!</text>
    <!-- labels on left -->
    <text x="20" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11" fill="#3B6D11" font-weight="500">🛑 STOP</text>
    <text x="20" y="97" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#3B6D11">here</text>
    <line x1="60" y1="88" x2="218" y2="82" stroke="#3B6D11" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arr)"/>
    <text x="20" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="11" fill="#633806" font-weight="500">🔁 LOOP</text>
    <text x="20" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="#633806">back</text>
