<div class="box box-amber">
  <strong>📋 The Cambridge exam task (Question 1 from the past paper)</strong>
  You are given an iterative function that counts lowercase vowels in a string. Your job: rewrite it recursively as <code>RecursiveVowels()</code>. Let's understand both versions.
</div>

<div class="sec-title">The iterative version (given to you)</div>
<pre class="py"><span class="kw">def</span> <span class="fn">IterativeVowels</span>(Value):
    Total = <span class="nm">0</span>
    <span class="kw">for</span> X <span class="kw">in</span> <span class="fn">range</span>(<span class="fn">len</span>(Value)):
        <span class="kw">if</span> Value[<span class="nm">0</span>] <span class="kw">in</span> <span class="st">'aeiou'</span>:
            Total += <span class="nm">1</span>
        Value = Value[<span class="nm">1</span>:]   <span class="cm"># chop off the first letter each time</span>
    <span class="kw">return</span> Total</pre>

<div class="fun-box fun-box-yellow" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
  <span class="emoji-big">💡</span><strong>How to turn this into recursion — the 3-question trick:</strong><br>
  1️⃣ <strong>What's the base case?</strong> → When the string is EMPTY (<code>""</code>), there are 0 vowels. Stop there!<br>
  2️⃣ <strong>What's the general case?</strong> → Check the FIRST letter. If it's a vowel, count 1. Then call yourself on the REST of the string.<br>
  3️⃣ <strong>Does it get smaller each call?</strong> → Yes! The string gets one character shorter each time. ✅
</div>

<div class="sec-title">The recursive version (what you write)</div>
<pre class="py"><span class="kw">def</span> <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value):
    <span class="cm"># BASE CASE 🛑 — empty string has 0 vowels</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> Value == <span class="st">""</span>:
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span>

    <span class="cm"># Is the first character a vowel?</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> Value[<span class="nm">0</span>] <span class="kw">in</span> <span class="st">'aeiou'</span>:
        <span class="cm"># YES → count 1 + call ourselves on the REST (everything after [0])</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">1</span> + <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value[<span class="nm">1</span>:])
    <span class="kw">else</span>:
        <span class="cm"># NO  → count 0 + call ourselves on the REST</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span> + <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value[<span class="nm">1</span>:])

<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(<span class="st">"house"</span>))    <span class="cm"># → 3  (o, u, e)</span>
<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(<span class="st">"imagine"</span>))  <span class="cm"># → 4  (i, a, i, e)</span></pre>

