    <div class="answer-block" id="r0-ans">
<pre><span class="cm"># Base case [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># if n == 0 → prints "Blastoff!" and returns WITHOUT calling countdown() again.</span>
<span class="cm"># This is the STOPPING condition.</span>

<span class="cm"># General case [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># countdown(n - 1) → calls itself with n-1 (a smaller number).</span>
<span class="cm"># Each call reduces n by 1, so it gets closer to 0 (the base case) each time.</span>
<span class="cm"># For countdown(3): prints 3, calls countdown(2)</span>
<span class="cm">#                   prints 2, calls countdown(1)</span>
<span class="cm">#                   prints 1, calls countdown(0)</span>
<span class="cm">#                   prints "Blastoff!" → stops</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="ex-citation">📌 Concept check — Chapter 24</div>
  </div>
</div>

