<!-- EX R2 -->
<div class="ex">
  <div class="ex-head" onclick="toggle('r2')">
    <div class="ex-head-left"><span class="ex-num">R2</span><span class="ex-title">Write RecursiveVowels() — Cambridge 9618/41/O/N/23 Q1(b)(i)</span></div>
    <div class="ex-meta"><span class="badge badge-easy">Easy</span><span class="badge badge-marks">[6 marks]</span><span class="toggle-lbl" id="r2-lbl">▼ expand</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-body" id="r2" style="display:none;">
    <div class="scenario">
      The iterative function <code>IterativeVowels(Value)</code> counts lowercase vowels (a, e, i, o, u) in a string.<br><br>
      <strong>Rewrite it as a recursive function</strong> with the identifier <code>RecursiveVowels()</code>.<br><br>
      The function must: take a string parameter, count lowercase vowels recursively, and return the total count as an integer.
    </div>
    <ul class="task-list">
      <li>Identify the base case for this recursive function. <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>Identify the general case. What is the recursive call? <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>Write the complete program code for <code>RecursiveVowels()</code>. <span class="pts">[4]</span></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tip-box"><strong>Base case:</strong> empty string → 0 vowels. <strong>General case:</strong> check first character (<code>Value[0]</code>) then call yourself on the rest (<code>Value[1:]</code>).</div>
    <div class="btn-row"><button class="hint-btn" onclick="showHint('r2')">💡 Hint</button><button class="answer-btn" onclick="showAnswer('r2')">Show Answer</button></div>
    <div class="hint-box" id="r2-hint">
      Base case: <code>if Value == "": return 0</code>.<br>
      Check: <code>if Value[0] in 'aeiou'</code> → return 1 + RecursiveVowels(Value[1:])<br>
      Otherwise → return 0 + RecursiveVowels(Value[1:])
    </div>
    <div class="answer-block" id="r2-ans">
<pre><span class="cm"># Base case [1 mark]: when string is empty → 0 vowels</span>
<span class="cm"># General case [1 mark]: check first character, call on Value[1:] (rest of string)</span>

<span class="kw">def</span> <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value):
    <span class="cm"># BASE CASE 🛑 — empty string, no more characters to check</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> Value == <span class="st">""</span>:
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span>
    <span class="cm"># GENERAL CASE 🔁</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> Value[<span class="nm">0</span>] <span class="kw">in</span> <span class="st">'aeiou'</span>:
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">1</span> + <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value[<span class="nm">1</span>:])
    <span class="kw">else</span>:
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span> + <span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(Value[<span class="nm">1</span>:])

<span class="cm"># [1] Correct function header with parameter</span>
<span class="cm"># [1] Base case: empty string returns 0</span>
<span class="cm"># [1] Checks first character (Value[0]) against vowels</span>
<span class="cm"># [1] Recursive call on Value[1:] (string with first char removed)</span>

<span class="cm"># Test:</span>
<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(<span class="st">"house"</span>))    <span class="cm"># → 3</span>
<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">RecursiveVowels</span>(<span class="st">"imagine"</span>))  <span class="cm"># → 4</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="ex-citation">📌 Source: 9618/41/O/N/23 Q1(b)(i)</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EX R3 -->
<div class="ex">
  <div class="ex-head" onclick="toggle('r3')">
    <div class="ex-head-left"><span class="ex-num">R3</span><span class="ex-title">What's missing? Fix the broken recursive function 🔧</span></div>
    <div class="ex-meta"><span class="badge badge-mid">Intermediate</span><span class="badge badge-marks">[3 marks]</span><span class="toggle-lbl" id="r3-lbl">▼ expand</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-body" id="r3" style="display:none;">
    <div class="scenario">
      A student wrote this recursive function to add up all numbers from 1 to n (e.g., sum(4) = 4+3+2+1 = 10). But it has a bug — it crashes every time!
      <pre style="margin:0.5rem 0;background:var(--paper3);padding:0.75rem;border-radius:5px;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:12.5px;">def sum_down(n):
    return n + sum_down(n - 1)</pre>
    </div>
    <ul class="task-list">
      <li>Explain why this function crashes. <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>State what is missing. <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>Write the corrected version of <code>sum_down()</code>. <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tip-box"><strong>Think:</strong> What are the TWO essential things every recursive function needs? Which one is missing here?</div>
    <div class="btn-row"><button class="hint-btn" onclick="showHint('r3')">💡 Hint</button><button class="answer-btn" onclick="showAnswer('r3')">Show Answer</button></div>
    <div class="hint-box" id="r3-hint">The function calls itself forever because it never stops. It needs a BASE CASE. When n == 0 (or 1), it should stop and return a value directly.</div>
    <div class="answer-block" id="r3-ans">
<pre><span class="cm"># Why it crashes [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># There is no base case (stopping condition). The function calls itself</span>
<span class="cm"># forever: sum_down(n) → sum_down(n-1) → sum_down(n-2) → ... endlessly.</span>
<span class="cm"># This fills the call stack completely → stack overflow crash. 💥</span>

<span class="cm"># What is missing [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># A base case — a condition that returns a value WITHOUT a recursive call.</span>

<span class="cm"># Corrected version [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="kw">def</span> <span class="fn">sum_down</span>(n):
    <span class="kw">if</span> n == <span class="nm">0</span>:           <span class="cm"># BASE CASE 🛑</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span>
    <span class="kw">else</span>:               <span class="cm"># GENERAL CASE 🔁</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> n + <span class="fn">sum_down</span>(n - <span class="nm">1</span>)

<span class="cm"># Test: sum_down(4) = 4 + 3 + 2 + 1 + 0 = 10</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="ex-citation">📌 Debug exercise — Chapter 24</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EX R4 -->
<div class="ex">
  <div class="ex-head" onclick="toggle('r4')">
    <div class="ex-head-left"><span class="ex-num">R4</span><span class="ex-title">Describe recursion — theory question 📝</span></div>
    <div class="ex-meta"><span class="badge badge-mid">Intermediate</span><span class="badge badge-marks">[4 marks]</span><span class="toggle-lbl" id="r4-lbl">▼ expand</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-body" id="r4" style="display:none;">
    <div class="scenario">
      A Cambridge examiner asks the following question:
    </div>
    <ul class="task-list">
      <li>Define what is meant by recursion. <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>State the TWO essential features every recursive algorithm must have. <span class="pts">[2]</span></li>
      <li>Give ONE benefit and ONE drawback of using recursion instead of iteration. <span class="pts">[2]</span></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tip-box"><strong>Exam technique:</strong> For "define", use the exact Cambridge keywords. For benefits/drawbacks, be specific — don't just say "it's faster/slower", say WHY.</div>
    <div class="btn-row"><button class="hint-btn" onclick="showHint('r4')">💡 Hint</button><button class="answer-btn" onclick="showAnswer('r4')">Show Answer</button></div>
    <div class="hint-box" id="r4-hint">
      Definition: "a function/procedure that calls itself".<br>
      Features: base case + general case.<br>
      Benefit: shorter/cleaner code. Drawback: uses more memory (stack frames).
    </div>
    <div class="answer-block" id="r4-ans">
<pre><span class="cm"># Definition [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># Recursion is a programming technique where a function (or procedure)</span>
<span class="cm"># calls itself as part of its own definition in order to solve a problem.</span>

<span class="cm"># Two essential features [2 marks]:</span>
<span class="cm"># [1] Base case — a stopping condition that returns a value WITHOUT</span>
<span class="cm">#     making another recursive call. Prevents infinite loops.</span>
<span class="cm"># [1] General (recursive) case — the part that calls the function again</span>
<span class="cm">#     with a smaller/simpler input, moving towards the base case.</span>

<span class="cm"># Benefit [1 mark] — any ONE of:</span>
<span class="cm"># • Code is shorter and easier to read for problems with a naturally</span>
<span class="cm">#   recursive structure (e.g. factorial, Fibonacci, tree traversal).</span>
<span class="cm"># • The code mirrors the mathematical definition of the problem directly.</span>

<span class="cm"># Drawback [1 mark] — any ONE of:</span>
<span class="cm"># • Uses more memory than iteration — every recursive call adds a new</span>
<span class="cm">#   stack frame, increasing memory usage significantly.</span>
<span class="cm"># • Risk of stack overflow if the base case is never reached (program crashes).</span>
<span class="cm"># • Slower execution than iterative solutions due to function call overhead.</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="ex-citation">📌 Theory question — Cambridge 9618 Chapter 24 style</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EX R5 — CHALLENGE -->
<div class="ex">
  <div class="ex-head" onclick="toggle('r5')">
    <div class="ex-head-left"><span class="ex-num">R5</span><span class="ex-title">Write your own recursive function — sum of digits 🔢</span></div>
    <div class="ex-meta"><span class="badge badge-hard">Challenge</span><span class="badge badge-marks">[5 marks]</span><span class="toggle-lbl" id="r5-lbl">▼ expand</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ex-body" id="r5" style="display:none;">
    <div class="scenario">
      Write a recursive function <code>SumDigits(n)</code> that takes a positive integer <code>n</code> and returns the sum of its digits.<br><br>
      For example: <code>SumDigits(123) = 1 + 2 + 3 = 6</code><br>
      <code>SumDigits(45) = 4 + 5 = 9</code><br><br>
      <strong>Hints:</strong> <code>n % 10</code> gives you the LAST digit. <code>n // 10</code> removes the last digit.
    </div>
    <ul class="task-list">
      <li>State the base case. What is the simplest input? What should be returned? <span class="pts">[1]</span></li>
      <li>State the general case. What digit do you add each call? What do you call recursively? <span class="pts">[2]</span></li>
      <li>Write the complete program code for <code>SumDigits(n)</code>. <span class="pts">[2]</span></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tip-box"><strong>Think through it:</strong> If n is a single digit (say 7), just return 7. If n has multiple digits, add the last digit (<code>n % 10</code>) to <code>SumDigits</code> of the rest (<code>n // 10</code>).</div>
    <div class="btn-row"><button class="hint-btn" onclick="showHint('r5')">💡 Hint</button><button class="answer-btn" onclick="showAnswer('r5')">Show Answer</button></div>
    <div class="hint-box" id="r5-hint">
      Base case: if n &lt; 10 (single digit), return n directly.<br>
      General case: return (n % 10) + SumDigits(n // 10).<br>
      SumDigits(123): last digit = 3, rest = SumDigits(12). Then SumDigits(12): last = 2, rest = SumDigits(1). SumDigits(1) = 1 (base). Total = 1+2+3 = 6.
    </div>
    <div class="answer-block" id="r5-ans">
<pre><span class="cm"># Base case [1 mark]:</span>
<span class="cm"># When n < 10 (single digit), return n directly.</span>
<span class="cm"># There's nothing more to split — the digit IS the answer.</span>

<span class="cm"># General case [2 marks]:</span>
<span class="cm"># Add the LAST digit (n % 10) to SumDigits of the REMAINING digits (n // 10).</span>
<span class="cm"># n // 10 removes the last digit → smaller input → gets closer to base case ✅</span>

<span class="cm"># Complete function [2 marks]:</span>
<span class="kw">def</span> <span class="fn">SumDigits</span>(n):
    <span class="kw">if</span> n < <span class="nm">10</span>:           <span class="cm"># BASE CASE 🛑 — single digit</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> n
    <span class="kw">else</span>:               <span class="cm"># GENERAL CASE 🔁</span>
        <span class="kw">return</span> (n % <span class="nm">10</span>) + <span class="fn">SumDigits</span>(n // <span class="nm">10</span>)

<span class="cm"># Trace of SumDigits(123):</span>
<span class="cm"># SumDigits(123): 123%10=3, call SumDigits(12)</span>
<span class="cm"># SumDigits(12):  12%10=2,  call SumDigits(1)</span>
<span class="cm"># SumDigits(1):   1 < 10 → BASE CASE → return 1</span>
<span class="cm"># Back: 2+1=3 → Back: 3+3=6</span>
<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">SumDigits</span>(<span class="nm">123</span>))  <span class="cm"># → 6 ✅</span>
<span class="fn">print</span>(<span class="fn">SumDigits</span>(<span class="nm">45</span>))   <span class="cm"># → 9 ✅</span></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="ex-citation">📌 Challenge exercise — Chapter 24</div>
  </div>
</div>

