<div class="before-exam">
  <h3>🧠 Before the Exam — Recursion Cheat Sheet</h3>
  <div class="be-section">── THE 2 RULES (NEVER FORGET) ───────────────────────────</div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">Base Case 🛑</span><span class="be-val">Stops recursion. Returns directly. No self-call. e.g. if n==0: return 1</span></div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">General Case 🔁</span><span class="be-val">Calls itself with SMALLER input. Gets closer to base case each time.</span></div>
  <div class="be-section">── DEFINITION (COPY THIS WORD FOR WORD) ─────────────────</div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">Recursion</span><span class="be-val">A function/procedure that calls itself as part of its own definition.</span></div>
  <div class="be-section">── FACTORIAL PATTERN (TEMPLATE) ─────────────────────────</div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">def f(n):</span><span class="be-val">if n == 0: return 1  ← base case</span></div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key"></span><span class="be-val">else: return n * f(n-1)  ← general case</span></div>
  <div class="be-section">── VOWELS PATTERN (EXAM QUESTION) ───────────────────────</div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">def RecursiveVowels(Value):</span><span class="be-val">if Value == "": return 0  ← base case (empty string)</span></div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key"></span><span class="be-val">if Value[0] in 'aeiou': return 1 + RecursiveVowels(Value[1:])</span></div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key"></span><span class="be-val">else: return 0 + RecursiveVowels(Value[1:])</span></div>
  <div class="be-section">── THE CALL STACK ────────────────────────────────────────</div>
  <div class="be-row"><span class="be-key">PUSH (going down ⬇)</span><span class="be-val">Each recursive call = new stack frame added on top</span></div>
